	year = {2010},
	keywords = {quadrupolar coupling, electric field gradient, quadrupolar splitting, NQR, central transition, satellite transitions, spin locking, MQMAS},
	abstract = {In this article, the reader is introduced to the fundamental concepts underlying NMR of quadrupolar nuclei in solid samples. In a section on the basic spin properties, the fundamental concepts of the nuclear quadrupolar coupling constant, the quadrupolar frequency, and the quadrupolar splitting are defined, while the characteristics of NMR and NQR spectra are introduced and compared. Typical values of quadrupolar coupling constants are tabulated. The following section is concerned with the behavior of quadrupolar spins under RF irradiation. It is followed by a survey of the wide range of experimental NMR methods developed for quadrupolar nuclei. While the descriptions mentioned so far keep quantum mechanical modeling and mathematical expressions to a minimum, the final section introduces the theoretical aspects of quadrupolar spin interactions.}
}

